18/11/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- A court in Belgrade on Wednesday (November 17th) sentenced former Serb paramilitary member Darko Radivoj to ten years in prison for war crimes.
Radivoj was found guilty of killing a wounded Croatian prisoner in the village of Tenja, eastern Croatia, in November 1991.
The trial against him started six months ago.
Radivoj has the right to appeal the sentence.
(RTRS, Radio Free Europe, Tanjug, S media - 17/11/10)
